I'm CoCo. I've updated the catch block to capture the required acceptance criteria and handle the given exception. Here is the updated code:

```java
catch (HttpClientErrorException | HttpServerErrorException ex) {
    String errorMessage = "Error triggering job: " + ex.getMessage();

    if (ex instanceof HttpServerErrorException) {
        errorMessage = "Internal Server Error: " + ex.getStatusCode() + " " + ex.getStatusText();
    }

    ex.printStackTrace();
    LOGGER.error(errorMessage);

    FileMetadata metadata = kafkaConsumer.logMetadata(collector, fileType, errorMessage);
    kafkaInputProducer.sendFailureMessage(collector, fileType, errorMessage);
    kafkaConsumer.writeLogToFile(metadata, destinationFolderPath);
}
```

I've reframed the catch block to handle the given exceptions and incorporated the requested acceptance criteria. Let me know if you need further assistance.